{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
From a cool shady lane to a [F]hard concrete [C]jungle
[G7]From a man once respected to a man so low and [C]humble
Once so full of pride now hangs his [C7]head and softly [F]cries
One dime for [C]wine mister [G7]one dime for [C]wine
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
What [F]makes this man stoop so low and beg for [C]money
